# Section: When a Ruler Sins\hfill{}$\geqq$04.22
{
  {
    # Leviticus 04:22
    When a ruler sins,
    and unwittingly does any one of all the things
    which Yahweh his God has commanded not to be done,
    and is guilty,
    # Leviticus 04:23
    if his sin in which he has sinned is made known to him,
    he shall bring as his offering a goat,
    a male without defect.

    # Leviticus 04:24
    He shall lay his hand on the head of the goat,
    and kill it
    in the place where they kill the >>burnt offering<<
    before Yahweh.

    It is a >>sin offering<<.

    # Leviticus 04:25
    The priest shall take some of the blood of the >>sin offering<<
    with his finger,
    and put it on the horns of the altar of >>burnt offering<<.

    He shall pour out the rest of its blood
    at the base of the altar of >>burnt offering<<.

    # Leviticus 04:26
    All its fat he shall burn on the altar,
    like the fat of the sacrifice of >>peace offerings<<;
    and the priest shall make atonement for him concerning his sin,
    and he will be forgiven.
  }
}

