# Section: \hfill{}$\geqq$05.14
# Leviticus 05:14
Yahweh spoke to Moses,
saying,
# Leviticus 05:15
{
  If anyone commits a trespass,
  and sins unwittingly
  regarding Yahweh's holy things,
  then he shall bring his >>trespass offering<< to Yahweh:
  a ram without defect from the flock,
  according to your estimation in silver by shekels,
  according to the shekel of the sanctuary,
  for a >>trespass offering<<.

  # Leviticus 05:16
  He shall make restitution for that which he has done wrong
  regarding the holy thing,
  and shall add a fifth part to it,
  and give it to the priest;
  and the priest shall make atonement for him
  with the ram of the >>trespass offering<<,
  and he will be forgiven.

  # Leviticus 05:17
  If anyone sins,
  doing any of the things which Yahweh has commanded not to be done,
  though he didn't know it,
  he is still guilty,
  and shall bear his iniquity.

  # Leviticus 05:18
  He shall bring a ram without defect from of the flock,
  according to your estimation,
  for a >>trespass offering<<,
  to the priest;
  and the priest shall make atonement for him
  concerning the thing in which he sinned and didn't know it,
  and he will be forgiven.

  # Leviticus 05:19
  It is a >>trespass offering<<.

  He is certainly guilty before Yahweh.
}

# Section: \hfill{}$\geqq$06.01
# Leviticus 06:01
Yahweh spoke to Moses,
saying,
# Leviticus 06:02
{
  If anyone sins,
  and commits a trespass against Yahweh,
  and deals falsely with his neighbor
  in a matter of deposit,
    or of bargain,
    or of robbery,
    or has oppressed his neighbor,
    # Leviticus 06:03
    or has found that which was lost,
      and lied about it,
      and swearing to a lie ---
  in any of these things that a man sins in his actions ---
  # Leviticus 06:04
  then it shall be,
  if he has sinned,
  and is guilty,
  he shall restore that which he took by robbery,
  or the thing which he has gotten by oppression,
  or the deposit which was committed to him,
  or the lost thing which he found,
  # Leviticus 06:05
  or any thing about which he has sworn falsely:
  he shall restore it in full,
  and shall add a fifth part more to it.

